# being.word — what a BEING is, has, and can. A presence a Name acts through.
# A being's name is its handle, lowercase. Its Name is the identity, capital.
# Bottoms out in the host (seed/materials/being/, identity/birth.js, the BE verb). Descends from
# word.word, base.word, chain.word, history.word, fold.word, name.word. `space`, `able`, and
# `qualities` ground in the noun cluster alongside. The BE verb's forms are elaborated in be.word.

A being is a presence, the fold of its fact chain.
A being is what a Name acts through. A Name acts in the world only through beings, and may have many.
A being has an id, the hash of its birth. The id is its presence, not its Name.
A being has a name, a word, on a history.
A being has a Name, the identity that acts and signs through it.
A being has a parent, a being before it.
A being has a home, a space.
A being has a home history, its present.
A being has a position, a space and a point in it.
A being has a able, and may have more granted.
A being has qualities, and its cognition is one.
A being may have an inhabitor, a Name that acts through it.
A being may have a father, a being that can connect into it.
A being may have a death. Its chain seals.
A being can be born.
A being can be connected to, and released.
A being can switch its history.
A being can die.
